China to Invest 40 Billion Yuan in New Drugs, Xinhua Says

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-10-15T01:40:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-15/china-to-invest-40-billion-yuan-in-new-drugs-xinhua-says.html
China will invest 40 billion yuan
($627 million) developing new medicine over the next five years,
the state-owned Xinhua News Agency reported today.  Total revenue in the drug-making industry will rise 20
percent annually to 3.1 trillion yuan by 2015, Xinhua said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tian Ying in Beijing at 
 ytian@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Tighe at 
 ptighe@bloomberg.net  